<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="197" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,780,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,1369,1395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,588,1370,1396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis box="[351,588,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis box="[715,736,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clarke" authorityYear="1876" box="[834,1098,1370,1396]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Strictae">
<emphasis box="[834,948,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1011,1098,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Strictae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its pinnately dentate leaves and solitary capitula. This species is distinct in its outer pappus plumose. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1061,1301,1405,1431]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis box="[1061,1301,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Saussurea pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang" authorityName="Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang" box="[250,742,1439,1465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis box="[250,431,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
Y. L. Chen &amp; S. Yun Liang
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, Y. L. &amp; Liang, S. Y. &amp; Pan, K. Y." box="[758,1003,1439,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" pagination="85 - 106" refId="ref6721" refString="Chen, Y. L., Liang, S. Y. &amp; Pan, K. Y. (1981) Taxa nova compositarum e flora Xizangensi (Tibetica). Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 19 (1): 85 - 106." type="journal article" year="1981">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[826,882,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">et al.</emphasis>
1981: 105
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lindley ex Royle 1835: 251) Wallich ex Candolle (1838: 532)" authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityPageNumber="532" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Lindley ex Royle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="251" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taraxacifolia">
<emphasis box="[1067,1240,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. taraxacifolia</emphasis>
(Lindley ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Royle, J. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="197" refId="ref7534" refString="Royle, J. F. (1835) Illustrations of the Botany and other Branches of the Natural History of the Himalayan Mountains, and the Flora of Cashmere, vol. 1. Wm. H. Allen and Co., London, 472 pp." type="book" year="1835">Royle 1835: 251</bibRefCitation>
) Wallich ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[392,632,1473,1500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" refId="ref6692" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1838) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, vol. 6. Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 687 pp." type="book" year="1838">Candolle (1838: 532)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its leaf shape. However 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[938,1084,1474,1500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis box="[938,1084,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in its usually stemless habit, caudex numerous branched, leaves sessile and linear-lanceolate, margin denate, capitula usually smaller, outer pappus plumose. A comparison of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[523,668,1545,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagriensis">
<emphasis box="[523,668,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. pagriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[682,862,1545,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis box="[682,862,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wallich ex Candolle" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Lindley ex Royle" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[917,1090,1544,1571]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taraxacifolia">
<emphasis box="[917,1090,1544,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">S. taraxacifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given in 
<tableCitation box="[1220,1309,1544,1570]" captionStart-0="TABLE 4" captionStart-1="TABLE 5" captionStartId-0="6.[136,224,1618,1642]" captionStartId-1="8.[136,224,1573,1597]" captionText-0="TABLE 4. Comparison of Saussurea pagriensis, S. purpurascens and S. taraxacifolia." captionText-1="TABLE 5. Comparison of Saussurea bhutanensis, S. columnaris and S. durgae." pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Table 4.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
